history.content: IMO I'd just apply now - applying isn't a commitment that you'll do it if you get an offer.

I am considering to apply for some reader positions to contribute back to the CS community. The priority deadline is approaching soon on March 31st, but I still have not finalized my plan for the summer yet as I am still waiting to hear back from my intern applications. I wonder whether I should apply now to catch the priority deadline or wait until I finalize plans for the summer?

Also, is the job scope for summer readers different from fall/spring readers? Thanks a lot!
